summary: Welcome to North Zeyn Street, likely one of the most genuinely original streets in Downtown Anaheim. This authentic craftsman bungalow is one of these homes. Built in 1919 as one of two nearly identical homes constructed right next door to each other for the Lautenbach and Links families. There is a beautiful front porch, shaded by a mature oak tree which motif matches the gorgeous bronze front door hardware. There is a formal living room and dining room that is unaltered by any “fad” and is pure with its unfinished wood trim, built in bookcases, secretary desk, leaded glass windows, built in buffet and graceful high ceilings.  The current owner built a kitchen to match the existing elements of the home. Plentiful cabinets, gorgeous vintage stove and lots of natural light.The third bedroom is a great office because of its size and offers a gorgeous permitted bathroom with marble flooring and subway tile wainscoting. The main Jack and Jill bath has a unique six foot long claw foot tub.  This home may be eligible for the Mills Act, very eligible, and will be ready for the new owner to follow through on this “badge of honor”.Located just blocks away from The Anaheim Packing House, Farmer’s Park and Center St. Promenade.

summary: Great Duplex in a Clean, Desirable area of Anaheim. The property has been maintained well and sits on a large enough lot to expand and to possibly add a unit to make it a triplex! Each unit is 1100 sq ft with AC, 2 Bedrooms, 1 Bath, and a Spacious Kitchen/Family area. Unit A has a newer kitchen (~2010). Both units have newer stoves (2014). Both units have Dual Paned Windows. Each unit has a single car Garage plus an uncovered Assigned Parking spot at the rear of the lot. There is parking space to store an RV for more potential income as well as a 3rd Garage which has been leased as a garage & storage unit for $200/mo in the past! The Coin-Op laundry on-site generates income every week! There are high 'pride of ownership' neighborhoods in the tract. The location is Excellent for Commuters with Great Freeway access. Public bus is down the street...hop on and go to Disneyland! The Anaheim Plaza and Anaheim Regional Medical Center are close along with a Walmart Superstore and other great markets and services. Anaheim High School is a few blocks away. Tenants pay for their own electricity and gas inside their unit. Landlord pays for trash, gas and electricity for laundry and outside lighting. Unit A tenants have occupied since 2012 and Unit B since 2005.

Remodeled kitchen with Travertine floor, granite counter tops, new stainless steel gas range, hood, dishwasher, sink,  refrigerator, and solid wood cabinets.  Two newly remodeled bathrooms with designer finishes. summary: Gorgeous, and beautifully maintained 5 bedroom, 2 bathroom Anaheim pool home. This home has a beautifully remodeled kitchen with custom cabinets, quartz countertops and built-ins for the microwave and refrigerator. Adjacent to the kitchen is the dinning area that leads to the large living room with brick fireplace and custom mantel. Downstairs also has the large master bedroom, and a large bathroom. The second downstairs bedroom can also be used as a family room or den. At the top of the stairs is the other remodeled bathroom with new tile floors, toilet and shower/tub with ceramic tiles. There are 3 more good size bedrooms, all with ceiling fans. The front of the house and 3 car garage have been refreshed with concrete siding and brick. The house has dual pane windows, central air conditioning and was completely repiped with above slab copper piping. Both the front and back yards have sprinklers with timers. On the sides of the house are gated areas that can be used as dog runs. The back yard is landscaped and has low voltage lights on timers, there is also a large wood patio with ceiling fans. The gorgeous salt water system pool and spa invites you to go for a swim and the fire pit and seating area want to keep you warm on summer night.

This fully renovated, luxury home features 3 beds/2 baths, 1,918 sq. ft. of living space with an attached 2-car garage with direct access. The beautifully landscaped front yard and stone-lined entry invites you into its interior with a fantastic open floor plan, which includes a lovely stone fireplace at the heart of the living room, a spacious formal dining room, and an open kitchen. This Chef’s kitchen is light and bright boasting dazzling granite counter tops with mosaic backsplashes, handcrafted cabinets, stainless-steel appliances, and a breakfast bar/center island. Brand new 30-yr roof, full copper plumbing, A/C and furnace, doors and dual-pane windows, and an enclosed 550 sq. ft. game room, all fully permitted! summary: In a quiet neighborhood surrounded by trees and wildlife, this single-story, 4 bedroom home with loft is elevated above the bustle of the city. Oversized windows flood the interior with natural light, illuminating vaulted ceilings and an open living space grounded by an inviting fireplace and new, light-hued carpet and tile.     The redesigned kitchen opens to the family room and features new cabinetry; granite countertops, extended bar; and recessed lighting. A bay window and glass doors invite you to step outside and enjoy the patio, pool and spa. By day, witness sweeping vistas of nearby mountains. By night, see the spectacular city lights.    The master suite opens to the patio by way of French doors. A full wall of mirrored closets makes the most of high ceilings and abundant natural light. The luxurious bath features a dual, granite-topped vanity with plentiful cabinets and glass-enclosed shower.    Retreat to a cozy loft with private bath that is a perfect office, playroom or second master suite. Clever details include a step-down seating area with built-in storage bench and skylight overhead.     This well-designed home is turn-key and ideal for small families or empty-nesters seeking a one-of-kind property in a private community.

summary: On a spacious corner lot this 4 bedroom, 2 bath home sits in a quiet Anaheim neighborhood:1502 square feet of living space and a 7062 square feet. Move in ready, this single level home has a completely remodeled kitchen with rich mocha cabinets, granite counters and porcelain tile floors. There is a stainless double sink and stove.Great meals will come from this kitchen. A large open living area has a wood burning fireplace, room for a family gathering place and dining area. The house has new windows and slider plus fresh paint inside and out. All bedrooms have high end laminate floors.The master suite has a built-in vanity adjacent to the bathroom. The 4th bedroom is currently being used as an office. Enjoy the Jacuzzi tub in the second bathroom--it has been updated also. Out front there is drought resistant landscaping and the backyard is waiting for you to add your personal touches. Don't miss the fruit trees out back. Easy freeway access there is also Target shopping nearby. For entertainment and excellent restaurants the Anaheim Packing District is just a couple miles away. It is a tourist attraction all by itself. Let’s not forget Disneyland and the nightly fireworks show. Everything you need is right here.

summary: Enjoy this beautiful 3 bedroom/3 bathroom corner end unit in the highly desirable, resort-style community of Monaco! Boasting 1,363 square feet of living space this condo is the largest floor plan that Monaco has to offer and it rarely comes onto the market! Nestled away in a premier location at the end of Portofino and with nobody above or below, the main living area showcases an adjoining dining room and living room, high vaulted ceilings, gas fireplace, and large dual paned windows framed with plantation shutters. The kitchen has been updated with granite countertops, an eat-in breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances, and an abundance of cabinet space. The balcony is conveniently situated right off the kitchen so that you can entertain family & friends or simply relax and enjoy the serenity of Anaheim Hills! The main hallway leads to the master bedroom with ensuite bathroom accentuated by dual sinks and a spacious walk-in closet. The 3rd bedroom and full bathroom is perfect for family, guests, or that much needed home office. $195 HOA dues provide you access to the oversized pool & spa, workout gym, tennis courts, and clubhouse. Centrally located to the 91 freeway, toll roads, and local shops & restaurants you truly can work and play where you live!

Hidden away on an intimate cul-de-sac high in Anaheim Hills is this lovingly updated home with park-like yard set against a serene wooded backdrop. Interior amenities include hardwood flooring, all new travertine entry, custom staircase, raised panel doors, new bathrooms and hardware, dual pane windows, and a neutral paint palette throughout. The inviting double door entry opens to the living room with soaring beamed ceilings and plantation shutters, and the adjacent formal dining room. The gourmet island kitchen boasts custom cabinetry, granite countertops, professional Wolf range, breakfast nook and opens to the oversized family room with built-in media center. Retire upstairs to the large master suite with new spa-like shower and gorgeous custom cabinetry. Relax in the peaceful tree-lined yard in the saltwater pool and spa, entertain at the barbecue center with bar, and enjoy the fire pit and lush green lawn. Complete with a 3 car garage, this 4 bedroom, 2 and a half bath home has the location, floor plan, and amenities you have been waiting for.

summary: Perfectly situated on a cul-de-sac lot. Well manicured back yard oasis with iron fencing, two patios, retractable awning, and vinyl fenced patio featuring dramatic panoramic city and mountain views. Wonderful curb appeal and a double door entry opens to bright living areas featuring vaulted ceilings, dual pane windows, and plantation shutters. The chef's kitchen features honey maple cabinetry with roll out drawers, granite counters, island bar, recessed lighting, stainless steel appliances and two pantries. The downstairs features tile flooring, formal living and dining areas, an open kitchen to family room, and an optional downstairs bedroom or office with full bath. The upstairs includes two spacious bedrooms with mirrored wardrobes and two upgraded baths with matching cabinetry and granite counters to the kitchen. The large master suite features double door entry, an oversized master closet, plus both a soaking tub and walk-in shower. Overlooking the lower level is a cozy loft which can be configured as a library, stationary bike station or child's play area. Newer water heater and furnace, paneled doors, scraped ceilings, and ceiling fans.  Direct access garage and indoor laundry room with extensive additional storage cabinets and deep tub sink.

summary: 2 Houses on a lot in the Anaheim Colony Historic District. The front home was originally built in 1898 and might possibly qualify for the Mills Act. Rear unit is 700 sq.ft. 1 bedroom & 1 bath unit built in 1980. Centrally located blocks from Downtown Anaheim, Disneyland, Honda Center, Anaheim Angels Stadium, Knott's Berry Farm, Cal State Fullerton, Fullerton College, and many popular shopping malls. summary: Sitting at the end of a pride of ownership cul-de-sac within Anaheim's "Colony" Historic District, this home has it all & more! As you approach the front porch you'll notice the glass inlaid front door which lets the light shine through the inviting open floor plan. The living room with its cozy brick fireplace has distressed wood flooring & a slider leading to the large enclosed patio. The gourmet kitchen is equipped with a 5 burner gas range, stainless steel appliances, breakfast bar, granite counter tops, tiled backsplash, rosewood cabinetry, recessed lighting & slate flooring, which opens to the formal dining room. There are 3 generous sized bedrooms & remodeled bath. The master suite with its adjoining bath has a large glass enclosed shower & ball & claw tub. The 288 sq. ft. basement has multiple possibilities, along with the permitted 393 sq. ft. 1 bed 1 bath remodeled guest house. Other amenities include interior laundry, newer central air, heat & electrical, copper plumbing, ceiling fans, covered patio, & a 2 car attached garage. Let's not forget that all this sits on an expansive 10,890 sq. ft. lot, conveniently located a few blocks from Pearson Park, schools, freeway access, and lively downtown Anaheim.
